<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole lucaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole lucaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucaris">Pheidole lucaris</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole lucaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole lucaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucaris">lucaris</taxonomicName>
, from a grove, referring to the type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">
Diagnosis A medium sized, concolorous brown member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group characterized in the major by a somewhat flattened head in side view; relatively long, abundant, erect hairs on the mesosoma, waist, and gaster; short, equilateral propodeal spine in side view; longitudinal carinulae (but no rugoreticulum) covering the anterior dorsal half of the head, with middle section of clypeus smooth; postpetiolar node seen from above trapezoidal; and mesosoma mostly smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">
Similar in some but not all of these traits to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33662" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalca">chalca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181863" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole delicata Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole delicata Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delicata">delicata</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181956" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole ulothrix Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole ulothrix Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ulothrix">ulothrix</taxonomicName>
, and differing in others, as well as in additional details of
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">body form, sculpturing, pilosity, and color, as variously indicated.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.82, HL 0.92, SL 0.54, EL 0.14, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.50, SL 0.40, EL 0.08, PW 0.28.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Color Major: body dark brown, appendages medium brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Minor: body medium brown, tarsi yellow, and remainder of appendages light brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">Biology The type colony was collected in Atlantic lowland rainforest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
